Beach Street, west from West Broadway, showing details of this locale after the removal of the old Sixth Avenue "El". The triangular park in the foreground lies between West Broadway and Varick Street. Beyond is the open space where the former St. Johns Park Freight Terminal stood. The buildings opened to view are on the west side of Hudson Street. Views 2 and 3 are from the extension of Sixth Ave. The last details solely the American Thread Co. Bldg.

July 12, 1939

West Broadway, west side, south from Beach Street, to show in the background the outstanding Western Union Building. Obscuring a portion of same is the Shuttleworth Building (formerly the Comet Warehouse) at Finn Square. To the right of center is North Moore Street with low buildings at its North Westerly and South Westerly corners.

July 12, 1939

P. L. Sperr
